<br>
And the question is, is the slight extra benefit you'd get from a larger mana pool in a catastrophe situation, worth the loss in ac/hp/resists you'd have to take to get that larger mana pool?  Yes, me having an extra 150 mana to get off an extra Chloroblast might save a life once or twice.  But I could only get that 150 mana at the expense of, say, 150 hp, 20 ac, and/or 10 MR.  And I figure the odds of that HP/AC/resist saving my life, so I'm alive to heal the group in that catastrophe, are at least as great as the odds of that 150 mana saving the tank's or chanter's life. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
