<br>
I reread my paragraph and I guess I didn't clearly state what I meant to state.  What I mean is:<br>
<br>
In a raid situation, of course the appropriate resist is more important, but given that you have adequate resists (and hp and to a much lesser extent ac), having more mana is going to help you and your raid out... In other words, in a regular situation, there probably is going to be little difference in performace between a druid with 1100ac, 200+ resist, and 3400 mana, and a 1100ac, 200+ resist, 2800mana druid.  In a raid situation, though, it's going to matter a lot more.<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaedanmoonshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaedan Moonshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/20/01 1:12:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is 200 WIS really important?</span><hr size=1> In dungeons, AC/HP are really going to help a lot more once you get your mana pool past about 2600.<br>
<br>
When you hit level 60 and you no longer hunt in dungeons, and all of your time is spent in raid situations, its best to just pump up your mana pool, hp, and resists.  It doesn't really matter what your ac is when, say... dozekar/vindicator/dain/etc.. are hitting you unless its over 1200.  A cleric with 1100 ac unbuffed with 3500 hp is going to drop just as fast as a druid with 900 ac and 3500 hp.  If you think you are dieing to fast, pump up your hp.  Druids almost never take melee damage unless the tanks are all dead, but they do take a lot of AE damage.  Its really best to just pump up your mana pool because in these long fights you are going to need to heal as much as possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessageRange?topicID=3169.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3286.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3350.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3169.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3169.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3169.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeU